foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: As reported in the Department of State’s FOIA Annual Report for FY 2011, the number of cases pending at the end of the fiscal year for State was 8,715. The discrepancy is due to data reconciliation, which is conducted to ensure the highest level of data integrity in the case tracking system.

foia:OtherDenialReason.foia:OtherDenialReasonDescriptionText: Cases closed and went directly to litigation

foia:ProcessedAppealSection.foia:FootnoteText: All of the Department's appeals in this section are processed through the Appeals Review Panel; therefore, this statistic includes appeals for the Office of Inspector General.

foia:OtherDenialReason.foia:OtherDenialReasonDescriptionText: All documents transferred to another agency

foia:ExpeditedProcessingSection.foia:FootnoteText: OIG Reported no Requests for Expedited Processing.

foia:FeeWaiverSection.foia:FootnoteText: OIG Reported no Requests for Fee Waivers.

foia:PersonnelAndCostSection.foia:FootnoteText: This year’s personnel and budget costs include data used towards personnel and costs for the new FOIA electronic case tracking system at the Department, as well as overtime for litigation-related costs.

foia:ProcessedConsultationSection.foia:FootnoteText: As reported in the Department of State’s FOIA Annual Report FY 2011, the number of consultations pending at the end of the fiscal year was 1,867. The discrepancy is due to data reconciliation, which is conducted to ensure the highest level of data integrity in the case tracking system.

foia:BackloggedRequestComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: Compared with the end of FY 2011, the Department’s backlog increased by approximately 33% during this fiscal year due to an increase in referrals and transitioning to a new FOIA case processing system.
